## {{ rule.title }}

{% set position = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
You are filing as **{{ position.filing_status_label }}** for tax year 2025. The Internal Revenue Code keys several thresholds to filing status, and this stage resolves those thresholds before any income or credit math runs.

For your status, the engine reads the following constants:

- The [26 U.S.C. § 63](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section63&num=0&edition=prelim) standard deduction is **{{ position.standard_deduction_2025_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**. It is subtracted from your AGI to produce taxable income at stage US25-08.
- The [26 U.S.C. § 1211(b)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1211&num=0&edition=prelim) annual capital-loss deduction limit is **{{ position.capital_loss_limit_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**. Any net capital loss above this cap rolls forward under [§ 1212](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1212&num=0&edition=prelim) and is reflected on [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 7a at stage US25-05.
- The [26 U.S.C. § 1411](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1411&num=0&edition=prelim) net investment income tax (NIIT) threshold is **{{ position.niit_threshold_usd | money(currency="USD") }}** of modified AGI. NIIT applies at 3.8 % to investment income above this threshold (stage US25-20).
- The IRS yearly average exchange rate for 2025 is **{{ position.eur_per_usd_yearly_average_2025 }} EUR per USD**. Every later euro-to-dollar conversion uses this rate.

{% if position.use_treaty_resourcing -%}
You **elected treaty re-sourcing** under the U.S.-Germany income tax treaty ([Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) worksheet). Stages US25-15 through US25-18 layer the treaty additional credit onto the baseline [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) foreign tax credit.
{% else -%}
You **did not elect treaty re-sourcing**; the U.S. graph stops at the baseline [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) foreign tax credit and treaty stages produce zero additional credit.
{% endif %}
{% if position.include_staking_in_niit -%}
Per your explicit position, **staking income is included in NIIT** at stage US25-20. Treatment of staking under [§ 1411](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1411&num=0&edition=prelim) is unsettled, so this is a documented manual position rather than a default.
{% else -%}
Per your explicit position, **staking income is excluded from NIIT** at stage US25-20.
{% endif %}

